  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_2a6b4fa088699701a6fa9ccecfb5c25d_18_1",
    "text": "The primary authors of this document are the staff members of the Unified Listing Team, Ecological Services Program.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.07294117647058823,
      0.09090909090909091,
      0.34509803921568627,
      0.1412121212121212
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_2a6b4fa088699701a6fa9ccecfb5c25d_18",
    "order": 4
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_2a6b4fa088699701a6fa9ccecfb5c25d_18_12",
    "text": "Action: Temporary rule; reallocation.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.36392156862745095,
      0.10242424242424242,
      0.6141176470588235,
      0.11575757575757575
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_2a6b4fa088699701a6fa9ccecfb5c25d_18",
    "order": 5
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_2a6b4fa088699701a6fa9ccecfb5c25d_18_13",
    "text": "suMMARY: NMFS is exchanging unused flathead sole Community Development Quota (CDQ) for yellowfin sole CDQ acceptable biological catch (ABC) reserves in the Bering Sea and Aleutian Islands management area. This action is necessary to allow the 2016 total allowable catch of yellowfin sole in the Bering Sea and Aleutian Islands management area to be harvested.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.3615686274509804,
      0.12363636363636364,
      0.6305882352941177,
      0.2503030303030303
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_2a6b4fa088699701a6fa9ccecfb5c25d_18",
    "order": 6
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_2a6b4fa088699701a6fa9ccecfb5c25d_18_2",
    "text": "Authority",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.07294117647058823,
      0.14727272727272728,
      0.1403921568627451,
      0.16
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_2a6b4fa088699701a6fa9ccecfb5c25d_18",
    "order": 7
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_2a6b4fa088699701a6fa9ccecfb5c25d_18_3",
    "text": "The authority for this action is section 4 of the Endangered Species Act of 1973, as amended (16 U.S.C. 1531 et seq.).",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.07294117647058823,
      0.16424242424242425,
      0.34509803921568627,
      0.21515151515151515
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_2a6b4fa088699701a6fa9ccecfb5c25d_18",
    "order": 8
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_2a6b4fa088699701a6fa9ccecfb5c25d_18_4",
    "text": "Dated: September 26, 2016. Stephen Guertin, Acting Director, U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service. [FR Doc.2016–24142 Filed 10–5–16; 8:45 am] BILLING CODE 4333-15-P",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.07137254901960784,
      0.21878787878787878,
      0.3168627450980392,
      0.2957575757575758
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_2a6b4fa088699701a6fa9ccecfb5c25d_18",
    "order": 9
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_2a6b4fa088699701a6fa9ccecfb5c25d_18_19",
    "text": "The Aleutian Pribilof Island Community Development Association has requested that NMFS exchange 80 mt of fl athead sole CDQ reserves for 80 mt of yellowfin sole CDQ ABC reserves under S 679.31(d). Therefore, in accordance with S 679.31(d), NMFS exchanges 80 mt of fl athead sole CDQ reserves for 80 mt of yellowfin sole CDQ ABC reserves in the BSAI. This action also decreases and increases the TACs and CDQ ABC reserves by the corresponding amounts. Tables 11 and 13 of the final 2016 and 2017 harvest specifications for groundfish in the BSAI (81FR 14773, March 18, 2016), and following revision (81 FR 64782, September 21, 2016), are revised as follows:",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.6509803921568628,
      0.24848484848484848,
      0.9254901960784314,
      0.49696969696969695
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_2a6b4fa088699701a6fa9ccecfb5c25d_18",
    "order": 10
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_2a6b4fa088699701a6fa9ccecfb5c25d_18_14",
    "text": "DATEs: Effective October 6, 2016 through December 31, 2016.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.3623529411764706,
      0.25333333333333335,
      0.5850980392156863,
      0.2787878787878788
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_2a6b4fa088699701a6fa9ccecfb5c25d_18",
    "order": 11
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_2a6b4fa088699701a6fa9ccecfb5c25d_18_15",
    "text": "FOR FURTHER INFORMATION CONTACT: Steve Whitney, 907–586–7228.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.3623529411764706,
      0.2824242424242424,
      0.6015686274509804,
      0.30666666666666664
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_2a6b4fa088699701a6fa9ccecfb5c25d_18",
    "order": 12
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_2a6b4fa088699701a6fa9ccecfb5c25d_18_16",
    "text": "SUPPLEMENTARY INFORMATION: NMFS manages the groundfish fi shery in the Bering Sea and Aleutian Islands management area (BSAI) according to the Fishery Management Plan for Groundfish of the Bering Sea and Aleutian Islands Management Area (FMP) prepared by the North Pacific Fishery Management Council under authority of the Magnuson-Stevens Fishery Conservation and Management Act. Regulations governing fishing by U.S. vessels in accordance with the FMP appear at subpart H of 50 CFR part 600 and 50 CFR part 679.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.3615686274509804,
      0.3096969696969697,
      0.636078431372549,
      0.49818181818181817
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_2a6b4fa088699701a6fa9ccecfb5c25d_18",
    "order": 13
  },
